"6:162:9" : {s: 6, a: 162, w: 9, r: "علم", t: "ٱلْعَٰلَمِينَ", l: "عَٰلَمِين", lc: 73, tl: "l-ʿālamīna", lb: "সকল জাতি, সৃষ্টিজগত",e: "(of) the worlds", b: "সমস্ত জগৎ/সকল জাতি", i: "semesta alam", f: 61, rm: "to mark/sign/distinguish, creations/beings, world, science/learning/knowledge/information, aware/know. By means of which one knows a thing, hence it signifies world or creation, because by it the Creator is known. alim (pl. ulama) - one who is learned/wise or knows."},
